Files: deps/darts-clone-0.32h/*
Copyright: 2008-2014, Susumu Yata
License: BSD-2-clause
Comment:
 Bundled unconditionally: OpenCC's .ocd Darts loader has no build-time
 "use system darts-clone" option (ENABLE_DARTS/USE_SYSTEM_DARTS were
 removed; Darts support is always compiled in), and darts-clone is not
 itself packaged in the Debian archive.

Files: plugins/jieba/deps/cppjieba/*
Copyright: 2013, Yanyi Wu and cppjieba contributors
License: MIT
Comment:
 Bundled unconditionally by the optional opencc-jieba binary package:
 cppjieba is a header-only segmentation library with no Debian archive
 package to depend on instead.

Files: deps/marisa-0.3.1/*
Copyright: 2010-2025, Susumu Yata
License: BSD-2-clause or LGPL-2.1-or-later
Comment:
 Not built or shipped by this packaging: debian/rules configures with
 -DUSE_SYSTEM_MARISA=ON and links against the libmarisa-dev package
 instead. A real Debian source upload would repackage the orig tarball
 (Files-Excluded) to drop this directory entirely; see
 debian/README.source.

Files: deps/rapidjson-1.1.0/*
Copyright: 2015 THL A29 Limited, a Tencent company, and Milo Yip
License: MIT
Comment:
 Not built or shipped by this packaging: debian/rules configures with
 -DUSE_SYSTEM_RAPIDJSON=ON and links against the rapidjson-dev package
 instead. See debian/README.source.

Files: deps/tclap-1.2.5/*
Copyright: 2003 Michael E. Smoot,
           2004 Michael E. Smoot and Daniel Aarno,
           2017 Google Inc.
License: MIT
Comment:
 Not built or shipped by this packaging: debian/rules configures with
 -DUSE_SYSTEM_TCLAP=ON and links against the libtclap-dev package
 instead. See debian/README.source.

Files: deps/googletest-1.15.0/*
Copyright: 2008, Google Inc.
License: BSD-3-clause
Comment:
 Not built or shipped by this packaging: debian/rules configures with
 -DUSE_SYSTEM_GTEST=ON and builds test binaries against the googletest
 source package's /usr/src/googletest instead (see
 debian/patches/0004-Use-system-googletest.patch). Test binaries are
 not shipped in any binary package regardless.

Files: deps/pybind11-2.13.1/*
Copyright: 2016, Wenzel Jakob
License: BSD-3-clause
Comment:
 Not built or shipped by this packaging: debian/rules configures with
 -DBUILD_PYTHON=OFF. Python bindings are out of scope for this
 packaging (see packaging/debian/SPLIT_PROPOSAL.md); Debian does not
 currently ship a python3-opencc binary package either.

Files: deps/google-benchmark/*
Copyright: 2015, Google Inc.
License: Apache-2.0
Comment:
 Not built or shipped by this packaging: debian/rules configures with
 -DENABLE_BENCHMARK=OFF.

